{
  "texts": [
    "Responding to these questions necessitates models to decline providing an answer as the information cannot be located in the given text.",
    "• TriviaQA (Joshi et al, 2017).",
    "The TriviaQA dataset covers 95K Q&A pairs, with an average of six associated evidence documents per question, constituting over 650K question-answer-evidence triplets.",
    "The questions are relatively intricate, demanding cross-sentence reasoning for answer identification, providing a closer representation of real-world scenarios.",
    "• TyDiQA (Clark et al, 2020)."
  ]
}